        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T20:04:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "not sure i understand the problem this functions solves.\naren\u0027t scheduler job and trigger namespaces orthogonal?\n\nare we trying to prevent users from shooting themselves in the foot by using same name for entities of two different kinds? does scheduler server also do that? we don\u0027t do that for acl_sets, do we?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 396,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 396,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "ece507b3da22db3ad5063c9a9645e62f3327655d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a8cc3d1a_befabc6f",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/generators.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 396,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T20:42:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem it solves is\n\ncore.builder(name \u003d \u0027builder\u0027, bucket \u003d \u0027ci\u0027, triggered_by\u003d[\u0027something\u0027])\ncore.builder(name \u003d \u0027builder\u0027, bucket \u003d \u0027findit\u0027, triggered_by\u003d[\u0027something else\u0027])\n\nHere \u0027builder\u0027 can\u0027t be used as a scheduler Job IDs for these two scheduler jobs because it is ambiguous. Instead \u0027builder-ci\u0027 and \u0027builder-findit\u0027 will be picked.\n\nWhen there\u0027s no ambiguity we use builder names for scheduler job IDs, to avoid painful migrations when switching from current hand-crafted configs (that use builder names for scheduler job IDs) to lucicfg.",
      "parentUuid": "fc8b2194_b314fbfb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 396,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 396,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "ece507b3da22db3ad5063c9a9645e62f3327655d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c472a6d3_db1e5b67",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/generators.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 396,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T21:46:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i see. i was confused by using a single node_to_id dict for both pollers and builders. I interpreted the intention as to disambiguate across builders and pollers, but in fact the intention is to disambiguate pollers-with-same-names-in-different-buckets and *independently* builders-with-same-names-in-different-buckets.\n\nconsider clarifying this by having two separate maps:\n\n  poller_to_id \u003d scheduler_disambiguate_ids(pollers)\n  builder_to_id \u003d scheduler_disambiguate_ids(builders)\n\nif done so, i believe use_name() is not longer needed because we are guaranteed that (bucket, name) combinations are unique per namespace (builders and pollers), since graph finalization would fail otherwise\n\nam I missing something?",
      "parentUuid": "a8cc3d1a_befabc6f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 396,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 396,
        "endChar": 31
      },
