    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8bc92dc6_9dcad921",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/rules/project.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T20:04:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why this isn\u0027t \u0027luci-scheduler.appspot.com\u0027?\n\nstepping back, letting users to specify hosts seems to be an invitation to make a mistake, i.e. they may attempt to specify a prod buildbucket and dev scheduler. Besides it exposes underlying services.\nI think this setting should be more coarse (deployment\u003d(prod|staging|dev))",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "ece507b3da22db3ad5063c9a9645e62f3327655d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2ec9dd21_064c7de3",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/rules/project.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-10T20:42:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I disagree. I really hate hardcoding our environment details into binaries. Besides, service URLs are leaking through various UIs and logs anyway, this is inevitable. And I think it is in fact helpful to give a hint to the config readers what\u0027s involved and where to find it.\n\nMixing environments should be forbidden on some other level (e.g. ACLs).",
      "parentUuid": "8bc92dc6_9dcad921",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "ece507b3da22db3ad5063c9a9645e62f3327655d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
